  "description": "Today&#8217;s episode highlights the service of World War II veteran William (Sam) Magee.  Sam tried to enlist in every branch of the Canadian Military at age 14.  After the loss of his father, he was the sole bread winner for his family and the military was the best place to earn enough to care for them.  At the age of 17, he managed to sneak past the recruiters and get enrolled in the Toronto Scottish Regiment.  During his training he [&#8230;]",
  "content:encoded": "<p>Today&#8217;s episode highlights the service of World War II veteran <a title=\"Sam Magee Bio\" href=\"http://samthegadfly.wordpress.com/biography/\" target=\"_blank\">William (Sam) Magee</a>.  Sam tried to enlist in every branch of the Canadian Military at age 14.  After the loss of his father, he was the sole bread winner for his family and the military was the best place to earn enough to care for them.  At the age of 17, he managed to sneak past the recruiters and get enrolled in the <a title=\"Toronto Scottish Regiment \" href=\"http://tsrpd.com/the-toronto-scottish-regiment-home-page.html\" target=\"_blank\">Toronto Scottish Regiment</a>.  During his training he discovered that the Canadian Army needed soldiers to become paratroopers.  This lead him and his friends, <a title=\"Dennis Flynn\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dennis_Flynn\" target=\"_blank\">Dennis Flynn</a> and Bill Dinette, to the <a title=\"1st Special Service Force\" href=\"http://www.firstspecialserviceforce.net/\" target=\"_blank\">1st Special Service Force</a> in Helena, Montana.</p>\n<p>Despite washing out on initial selection, and a few brushes with The King&#8217;s Regulations and Orders, he made it back to the Force known as &#8220;the New Kid&#8221;.</p>\n<p>I&#8217;m sure his story will capture you as it has me.</p>\n<p>Follow me on Twitter @MikeLacroix32</p>\n<p>You can support this site by shopping on <a title=\"Amazon.ca\" href=\"http://www.amazon.ca?_encoding=UTF8&tag=thecanamilihi-20\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon</a>.  You still enjoy Amazon&#8217;s great prices, but a portion of your purchase goes to supporting the show.</p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-362-51\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/CMHP-Episode-015-WO2-Sam-Magee-Part-1.mp3?_=51\" /><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/CMHP-Episode-015-WO2-Sam-Magee-Part-1.mp3\">http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/CMHP-Episode-015-WO2-Sam-Magee-Part-1.mp3</a></audio>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/3063275955_1b9b04b1c3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-364\" alt=\"3063275955_1b9b04b1c3\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/3063275955_1b9b04b1c3.jpg\" width=\"156\" height=\"300\" /></a></p>\n<p>Sam in his best tuxedo!</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/3064103744_fe36e3982b_o.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"3064103744_fe36e3982b_o\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/3064103744_fe36e3982b_o-212x300.jpg\" width=\"212\" height=\"300\" /></a></p>\n<p>17 Year Old Pte Magee in the Toronto Scottish Regiment</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/3064103692_250896b2f7_o.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-365\" alt=\"3064103692_250896b2f7_o\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/3064103692_250896b2f7_o-274x300.jpg\" width=\"274\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/3064103692_250896b2f7_o-274x300.jpg 274w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/3064103692_250896b2f7_o.jpg 643w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 274px) 100vw, 274px\" /></a></p>\n<p>The &#8216;New Kid&#8217; in the 1st Special Service Force</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-367\" alt=\"Crest\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Crest-146x300.gif\" width=\"146\" height=\"300\" /></p>\n<p>The insignia of the 1St Special Service Force</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/3084829212_4b510f94f4_o.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-368\" alt=\"3084829212_4b510f94f4_o\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/3084829212_4b510f94f4_o-300x186.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"186\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/3084829212_4b510f94f4_o-300x186.jpg 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/3084829212_4b510f94f4_o.jpg 840w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re Canadian, you must know how to teach people how to ski!!</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/war_6.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-369\" alt=\"war_6\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/war_6-300x220.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"220\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/war_6-300x220.jpg 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/war_6.jpg 432w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Sam Magee at an Airborne reunion with Jan de Vries, CM and CWO Mark Shannon, RSM of the Queen&#8217;s Own Rifles of Canada</p>\n",
